Suresh Kumar wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Thanks everybody. I take the short answer to be &quot;Yes&quot; it is okay to
&gt; POST with empty content and I wouldn&#39;t be violating HTTP or REST.
&gt; 

Actually, no, the short answer is the REST constraint, &quot;manipulation of
resources through representations.&quot;  Not having an entity doesn&#39;t
necessarily mean not having a representation, but that&#39;s what it
usually means.  If you don&#39;t have a representation, you don&#39;t have
REST, you have RMI.

-Eric
